rederick%20Forsyth%2C%20a%20British%20author%20of%20thrillers%20who%20frequently%20made%20the%20bestseller%20lists%2C%20sold%2070%20million%20books%20and%20saw%20his%20novels%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Day%20of%20the%20Jackal%2C%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Odessa%20File%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Dogs%20of%20War%2C%E2%80%9D%20among%20others%2C%20adapted%20into%20films%2C%20died%20on%20Monday%20at%20his%20home%20in%20Jordans%2C%20England.%20He%20was%2086%20years%20old.%20The%20New%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22William%20Earl%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2025%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Ffrederick-forsyth-dead-dies-the-day-of-the-jackal-1236423859%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22An%20AI%20startup%20raised%20%2424M%20to%20help%20media%20companies%20make%20high-quality%20video%20faster%20and%20cheaper.%20Here's%20its%20pitch%20deck.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Philippe%20and%20Fred%20Petitpont%2C%20founders%20of%20Moments%20Lab%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684451d13d5881a51c1afa11%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221786%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPhilippe%20and%20Fred%20Petitpont%2C%20founders%20of%20Moments%20Lab.%3Cp%3EMoments%20Lab%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMoments%20Lab%20raised%20a%20%2424%20million%20round%20to%20expand%20its%20AI%20tools%20for%20Hollywood%20and%20others.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20startup%20says%20it%20can%20help%20clients%20like%20WBD%20and%20Hearst%20make%20videos%20faster%20and%20cheaper.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECheck%20out%20the%20pitch%20deck%20it%20used%20to%20raise%20its%20latest%20round.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMoments%20Lab%20is%20part%20of%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-startups-netflix-marvel-lucasfilm-holllywood-deepfake-dubbing-vc-funding-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20startups%3C%2Fa%3E%20raising%20money%20to%20reshape%20Hollywood%20and%20related%20fields.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoments%20Lab%20provides%20tools%20that%20index%20video%20libraries%20and%20create%20new%20videos%20from%20raw%20footage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20recently%20raised%20%2424%20million%20in%20Series%20B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvcs-funding-startups-disrupt-future-entertainment-generative-ai-tech-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efunding%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Oxx%2C%20with%20participation%20from%20Orange%20Ventures%2C%20Kadmos%2C%20Supernova%20Invest%2C%20and%20Elaia%20Partners.%20It%20plans%20to%20use%20the%20funding%20to%20build%20on%20its%20existing%20tech%20and%20roll%20out%20an%20agentic%20AI%20tool.%20To%20date%2C%20it's%20raised%20%2437.4%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParis-based%20Moments%20Lab%20was%20founded%20by%20twin%20brothers%20Fred%20and%20Philippe%20Petitpont%20in%202016.%20Philippe%20was%20a%20product%20manager%20for%20French%20media%20company%20TF1%20Group%2C%20while%20Fred%20was%20a%20tech%20lead%20at%20French%20ad%20holding%20company%20Havas'%20BETC%20Digital.%20They%20say%20they%20saw%20a%20need%20for%20media%20and%20entertainment%20companies%20to%20produce%20more%20video%20at%20a%20lower%20cost%20to%20feed%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisney-netflix-amazon-wbd-max-paramount-peacock-strategy-shift-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egrowing%20streaming%20ecosystem%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Their%20clients%20include%20Warner%20Bros.%20Discovery%2C%20Banijay%20Entertainment%2C%20Fullwell%20Entertainment%2C%20Hearst%2C%20Thomson%20Reuters%2C%20Sinclair%2C%20and%20Amazon%20Ads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoments%20Lab's%20core%20tool%2C%20MXT-2%2C%20breaks%20down%20and%20indexes%20video%20footage%20into%20components%2C%20like%20people%20who%20are%20on%20screen%20and%20what%20they're%20doing%2C%20and%20generates%20descriptions%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20key%20pitch%20is%20that%20it%20saves%20users%20time%20and%20money.%20Philippe%20Petitpont%20said%20the%20tech%20can%20identify%20soundbites%20for%20clips%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoutube-not-netflix-is-big-threat-to-hollywood-analysis-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esocial%20media%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20things%20like%20trailers%20and%20highlight%20reels%20about%20seven%20times%20as%20fast%20as%20an%20employee%20could%2C%20citing%20internal%20research.%20He%20also%20said%20some%20clients%20have%20reported%20making%20twice%20as%20much%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhollywood-tv-movies-feeding-youtube-growth-long-form-viewing-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erevenue%20from%20social%20media%3C%2Fa%3E%20using%20the%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20them%2C%20it's%20a%20way%20to%20create%20new%20revenue%20streams%2C%26quot%3B%20Petitpont%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20referring%20to%20revenue%20from%20social%20media.%20%26quot%3BBefore%20now%2C%20it%20was%20very%20complicated%20for%20production%20companies%20to%20create%20a%20revenue%20stream%20because%20there%20was%20a%20huge%20need%20for%20humans%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20a%20very%20tedious%20task.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoments%20Lab's%20newer%20agentic%20AI%20tool%2C%20which%20it%20says%20Hearst%20is%20among%20those%20testing%2C%20takes%20raw%20video%20material%20and%20turns%20it%20into%20rough%20cuts%20using%20written%20prompts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPetitpont%20said%20the%20AI%20agent%20can%20do%20this%20at%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20time%20it%20takes%20people%20to%20do%20the%20work.%20He%20said%20its%20most%20promising%20application%20so%20far%20is%20in%20reality%20TV.%20Scripted%20TV%20is%20still%20a%20work%20in%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPetitpont%20said%20Moments%20Lab%20has%20gained%20momentum%20with%20Hollywood%20companies%20since%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20year%2C%20as%20they%20face%20pressure%20to%20make%20more%20shows%20at%20lower%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20demand%20from%20Netflix%2C%20Amazon's%20Prime%20Video%2C%20Peacock%2C%20is%20so%20strong%20that%20production%20companies%20need%20to%20produce%20more%20content%20than%20ever%20before%2C%20and%20they%20don't%20have%20more%20money%20to%20produce%20a%20show%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBeing%20able%20to%20produce%20at%20lower%20cost%20is%20more%20important%20than%20ever.%20That's%20where%20they're%20interested%20in%20using%20new%20approaches.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20tools%20are%20widely%20used%20in%20Hollywood%20to%20make%20production%20processes%20more%20efficient%20and%2C%20for%20now%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsora-ai-film-movies-openai-who-uses-special-effects-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egenerate%20short%20videos%20from%20text%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Hollywood%20is%20highly%20protective%20of%20its%20intellectual%20property%2C%20which%20is%20a%20barrier%20to%20adoption.%20Another%20is%20its%20labor%20unions%2C%20which%20worry%20that%20AI%20will%20replace%20their%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPetitpont%20said%20one%20of%20the%20most%20time-consuming%20parts%20of%20the%20sales%20process%20is%20assuring%20companies'%20legal%20teams%20that%20it%20won't%20use%20their%20IP%20to%20train%20its%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoments%20Lab%20says%20its%20model%20is%20trained%20on%20a%20dataset%20of%201.5%20billion%20assets%20that%20it%20describes%20as%20a%20mix%20of%20open-source%20content%20and%20content%20from%20partners%20that%20are%20part%20of%20its%20research%20program%20(a%20consortium%20of%20research%20labs%2C%20media%20rights%20owners%2C%20and%20tech%20companies).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20doesn't%20shy%20away%20from%20the%20idea%20that%20automating%20work%20done%20by%20assistant%20editors%20and%20others%20can%20reduce%20the%20need%20for%20human%20workers.%20Petitpont%20said%20one%20US%20financial%20media%20client%20told%20him%20it%20expects%20to%20use%20fewer%20editors%20as%20a%20result%20of%20using%20its%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20big%20question%20is%3A%20Will%20the%20assistant%20start%20to%20be%20the%20senior%20editor%2C%20or%20will%20the%20job%20disappear%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20know%20yet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20there%20seems%20to%20be%20broad%20agreement%20on%20in%20the%20industry%20is%20that%20AI%20usage%20will%20grow%20%E2%80%94%20not%20only%20to%20save%20time%20on%20pre-%20and%20post-production%20functions%2C%20but%20make%20high-quality%20original%20video%20fast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20startups%20that%20tackle%20film%20editing%20functions%20include%20Runway%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpitch-deck-filmustage-aims-to-streamline-hollywood-work-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFilmustage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flift.comcast.com%2Fportfolio%2Fcompanies%2Fimaginario%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EImaginario%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPetitpont%20said%20the%20ability%20for%20media%20companies%20to%20use%20AI%20to%20help%20make%20full-length%20documentaries%20based%20on%20their%20video%20libraries%20is%20only%20several%20months%20off%2C%20imagining%20a%20company%20building%20a%20film%20on%20the%20history%20of%20America%20using%20decades%20of%20news%20footage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20year%2C%20he%20expects%20Moments%20Lab%20to%20be%20able%20to%20provide%20predictive%20modeling%20tools%20that%20will%20make%20suggestions%20about%20changes%20to%20a%20video%20that%20could%20boost%20its%20audience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20what%20we%20believe%20will%20be%20the%20next%20thing%2C%20and%20we're%20not%20very%20far%20from%20that%20because%20audience%20data%20is%20very%20easily%20available%20on%20YouTube%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20tech%20is%20not%20the%20issue%2C%20it's%20more%20the%20rights.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECheck%20out%20key%20slides%20f