y're%20%26quot%3Bconstantly%20being%20evaluated%20or%20scrutinized%2C%26quot%3B%20Goldberg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20of%20our%20staff%20are%20junior%20and%20midlevel%20employees%20hungry%20to%20learn%2C%20grow%2C%20and%20evolve%2C%26quot%3B%20Goldberg%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20very%20receptive%20to%20feedback%2C%20and%20we've%20heard%20from%20nearly%20all%20that%20they%20prefer%20real-time%2C%20ongoing%20feedback%20rather%20than%20formal%20review%20meetings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoldberg%20said%20they%20started%20with%20monthly%20check-ins%20based%20on%20custom%20goals%20and%20expectations%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleadership-motivates-employees-return-to-the-office-jll-neil-murray-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esenior%20leadership%3C%2Fa%3E%20documented%20for%20each%20staff%20member.%20The%20frequency%20evolved%20into%20quarterly%20or%20twice-a-year%20check-ins%2C%20depending%20on%20each%20employee's%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoldberg%20said%20that%20creating%20a%20direct%20line%20of%20communication%20to%20the%20senior%20leadership%20team%20has%20helped%20employees%20%26quot%3Bforge%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbcg-consulting-two-way-mentorship-inclusion-drive-talent-innovation-ai-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ementor%20relationships%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20learn%20and%20grow%20in%20a%20positive%2C%20constructive%20format.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESarah%20Schmidt%2C%20the%20president%20of%20Interdependence%2C%20a%20Chicago-based%20PR%20and%20strategic%20communications%20firm%2C%20told%20BI%20she%20uses%20real-time%20feedback%20with%20her%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnnual%20reviews%20felt%20absurd.%20Why%20wait%20six%20months%20to%20fix%20something%20you%20could%20solve%20in%20six%20minutes%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchmidt%20formalized%20the%20review%20process%20at%20Interdependence%20when%20she%20joined%20the%20firm%20about%20four%20years%20ago.%20The%20process%20involves%20twice-a-month%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-career-coach-accessible-employee-coaching-professional-development-2025-4%3Futm_source%3Dchatgpt.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecoaching%3C%2Fa%3E%20check-ins%2C%20which%20are%20guided%20by%20relevant%20projects%20and%20key%20performance%20indicators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchmidt%2C%20who%20has%20managed%20teams%20for%20over%2012%20years%2C%20said%20that%20employees%20might%20be%20skeptical%20of%20a%20continuous%20feedback%20style%2C%20especially%20if%20they're%20used%20to%20annual%20reviews.%20But%20if%20it's%20done%20right%2C%20everyone%20wins%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BContinuous%20input%20requires%20discipline%2C%26quot%3B%20Schmidt%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20trained%20our%20leaders%20to%20deliver%20bite-sized%2C%20actionable%20notes%20instead%20of%20saving%20up.%20Today%2C%20the%20most%20common%20praise%20we%20hear%20is%2C%20'Leadership%20feels%20like%20a%20partner%20in%20my%20growth%2C'%20which%20is%20music%20to%20my%20ears.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22488cbfbe-6192-4b0d-be0b-c0be41f3a38a%5C%22%3EOngoing%20feedback%20can%20pay%20off%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETim%20Duba%2C%20the%20cofounder%20of%20wellness%20company%20Protekt%20Products%2C%20said%20that%20ongoing%20feedback%20can%20help%20reduce%20the%20fear%20of%20being%20wrong%2C%20which%20can%20impact%20employee%20collaboration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20feedback%20is%20constant%20and%20normalized%2C%20people%20stop%20being%20precious%20about%20their%20ideas%2C%26quot%3B%20Duba%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20care%20where%20a%20good%20idea%20comes%20from.%20We%20care%20if%20it%20works.%20Mistakes%20aren't%20failures%20here%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20data%20points.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20using%20this%20approach%20at%20Protekt%20Products%20led%20the%20company%20to%20bring%20manufacturing%20and%20fulfillment%20in-house%2C%20which%20one%20of%20his%20employees%20had%20suggested.%20This%20type%20of%20change%20can%20be%20costly%20and%20risky%2C%20he%20said%2C%20but%20open%20communication%20allowed%20employees%20across%20the%20company%20to%20adjust%20to%20the%20change%20collaboratively.%20He%20said%20the%20business%20move%20has%20set%20the%20company%20up%20to%20triple%20its%20growth%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuba%20said%20continuous%20feedback%20also%20gave%20employees%20clarity%20and%20eliminated%20guesswork%2C%20creating%20a%20%26quot%3Bmore%20organized%2C%20decisive%2C%20and%20focused%26quot%3B%20work%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTrust%20builds%20quickly%20when%20you%20know%20your%20strengths%20and%20weaknesses%2C%20and%20your%20teammates%20do%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20Duba%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20move%20faster%20because%20people%20know%20their%20lane%20and%20how%20to%20win%20in%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Interdependence%2C%20the%20idea%20for%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpinterest-hackathons-makeathon-employees-lead-generative-ai-tools-innovation-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20training%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20certificate%20program%20came%20about%20from%20a%20junior%20staff%20member's%20suggestion%20in%20a%20coaching%20chat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLeadership%20greenlit%20a%20two-week%20training%20sprint%3B%20now%20it's%20a%20firm-wide%20curriculum%20that%20upskills%20every%20team%20member%20and%20helps%20us%20work%20smarter%2C%20faster%2C%20and%20deliver%20for%20our%20clients%20more%20efficiently%2C%26quot%3B%20Schmidt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ed7128fb-5682-404b-9a26-92576762e178%5C%22%3EBuilding%20better%20work%20habits%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESchmidt%20said%20that%20if%20overhauling%20a%20feedback%20system%20seems%20daunting%2C%20start%20small%20and%20focus%20on%20quick%20exchanges.%20She%20suggested%20starting%20with%20a%20simple%20cadence%20%E2%80%94%20like%2015-minute%20check-ins%20every%20other%20week%20%E2%80%94%